---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About Staretz Blog">
  <main class="max-w-2xl flex flex-col items-center m-auto">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">About the Blog</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-xl text-gray-300 leading-relaxed font-sans">
      <p>
        This simpler version of the Staretz blog is built using <span
          >Astro</span
        > and Tailwind CSS.
      </p>
      <p>
        By leveraging strict TypeScript guidelines, we extract application state
        to <span>Signals</span>, and utilize a Hexagonal architecture per our AI
        Agent Guidelines. This ensures our core logic remains entirely decoupled
        from UI frameworks.
      </p>
      <p>
        As an architectural exercise, all routing is file-based and the design
        uses a minimalist black theme with Inconsolata and striking <span
          >magenta</span
        > accents.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
